Status-based one-time activation for license keys

Changed license validation from IP-based session locking to pure
status-based one-time activation:

- Validate endpoint: if key status is "active", deny with "License
  already activated" — no IP checks, purely based on status
- Once a key is activated (pending → active), it cannot be validated
  again by anyone
- Heartbeats still work for the running session
- Removed check_session_lock function entirely
- Removed IP-based session locking logic from both validate and heartbeat

Dashboard changes:
- Added "Reset" button for active keys — resets status back to "pending"
  so the key can be activated again
- Added .btn-warning style (orange) for the Reset button
- Reset clears activated_at, last_ip, last_heartbeat

Launcher changes:
- Removed is_in_use special case — all errors (expired, revoked,
  already activated) now delete the saved key file
- Simplified watchdog error handling
